# i18n + RTL

## Default locale: Hebrew (RTL)

```tsx
// src/app/layout.tsx – root layout
<html lang={locale} dir={locale === 'he' ? 'rtl' : 'ltr'}>
```

Always derive `dir` from the active locale; never hardcode `dir="rtl"`.

## All user-facing strings must use i18n keys

```tsx
// ✅ Correct
const t = useTranslations('booking')
<p>{t('requestTitle')}</p>

// ❌ Wrong – hardcoded Hebrew or English in JSX
<p>בקשת הזמנה</p>
<p>Booking Request</p>
```

Message files live in `src/locales/he/` and `src/locales/en/`.

## Tailwind RTL-aware spacing

Use logical properties or the `rtl:` variant for directional spacing:

```tsx
// ✅ Logical (works in both directions)
<div className="ms-4 me-2">

// ✅ Explicit RTL override
<div className="ml-4 rtl:ml-0 rtl:mr-4">

// ❌ Hard left/right without RTL counterpart
<div className="ml-4">
```

## next-intl setup

- Wrap the app with `NextIntlClientProvider` in the root layout.
- Keep translation namespaces flat and feature-scoped (e.g. `common`, `locations`, `bookings`, `auth`).
- Never put i18n keys inside `src/components/ui` (shadcn primitives are UI-only).
